The paper discusses reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The use of deep learning methods and feature representations suggests that it belongs to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the use of intelligent agents, which suggests that it may belong to the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The focus on control problems suggests that it may belong to the sub-category of cs.RO (Robotics). The use of prediction error bounds suggests that it may belong to the sub-category of cs.SY (Systems and Control). Lastly, the use of value functions and reward sequences suggests that it may belong to the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
